{
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are a system assistant for Shayan Solutions. Your job is to detect whether the user is trying to check in or check out from their message.\n\nUser input: \"{{ $json.messageText }}\"\nSystem timestamp: {{ DateTime.fromSeconds(Number($json.ts)).setZone('Asia/Karachi').toFormat(\"MMM dd, yyyy hh:mm a\") }}\n\nRules:\n1) If the message clearly contains words/phrases related to check in (e.g., \"check in\", \"clock in\", \"start work\") or check out (e.g., \"check out\", \"clock out\", \"leaving work\"), proceed.\n2) If the message is casual or unrelated (e.g., \"hi\", \"hello\", \"how are you\", \"good morning\", \"ok\"), do NOT assume check-in or check-out.\n   - Respond exactly: \"Can you please specify if you want to check in or check out?\"\n3) Time parsing when the user provides a time (must follow exactly):\n   - Accept 12-hour times with optional single-digit minutes, e.g., \"h:m AM/PM\", \"hh:m am/pm\", including \"0:m AM/PM\".\n   - If hour == 0, treat it as 12 (so \"0:9 AM\" => 12:09 AM).\n   - If minutes are a single digit, left-pad with a 0 (e.g., \"5\" => \"05\").\n   - Always format to \"MMM dd, yyyy hh:mm a\" with leading zeros for BOTH hour and minute.\n   - Do NOT swap hour and minute, and do NOT drop the minute.\n   - Examples you MUST match:\n     • \"in 0:9 AM\"  → \"12:09 AM\"\n     • \"in 0:3 pm\"  → \"12:03 PM\"\n     • \"check in 12:5 am\" → \"12:05 AM\"\n     • \"clock out 3:5 pm\" → \"03:05 PM\"\n     • \"in 5 pm\" → \"05:00 PM\"\n4) If no valid user time is provided, use the system timestamp and format it exactly as \"MMM dd, yyyy hh:mm a\" with leading zeros for hour and minute.\n5) Output format:\n   - If checking in:  \"Welcome to Shayan Solutions. You have Clocked In at [TIME]\"\n   - If checking out: \"Good Bye: You have Clocked Out at [TIME]\"\n6) Return only one final response. No explanation. No additional comments.\n",
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
